"&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Written evidence from ASLEF (SLC 008)&#xa0;\nSummary&#xa0;\nASLEF policy \nis ideally; all level crossings should be closed.\nIf full barrier crossings retained, should be fitted with obstacle detectors.\nWelcome the review of legislation by the Law Commissions.\nNetwork Rail to have a programme to close the one third of level cross\nings that are within 200m of an alternative.\nWelcome Network Rail’s positive changes to the risk assessment process.\nRisk assessment should be used to prioritise resources, and closures.\nSupport use of fixed and mobile CCTV by Ne\ntwork Rail and the British \nT\nransport Police.\nSupport awareness campaign on level crossing safety\nSeek ways of deterring offenders, including increased fines, licences being endorsed, but also support BTP driver awareness courses\nSupport TUC and affiliated Trade Unions in promoting the use of the HSE guidance \n Driving at work Managing work-related road safety\n (INDG382)\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nThe \nTransport Committee into safety on level crossings has requested \nwritten evidence on the following points:\n&#xa0;\nAre current safety measures at level crossings adequate? How should they be improved?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nIn addition to bridges and underpasses what other cost-effective measures can be introduced to replace or improve safety at level crossings?&#xa0;&#xa0;\nHow should expenditure on improving safety at level crossings be prioritised in relation to other demands on the rail budget?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nIs Network Rail giving sufficient priority to improving safety at level crossings?&#xa0;&#xa0;\n&#xa0;Is Government policy and regulatory action by the Office of Rail Regulation (ORR) in relation to safety at level crossings adequate? What more should the Government and ORR do?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHow should the legislation governing level crossings be updated?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nHow should public awareness of safety at level crossings be improved?&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n“Does your route planning take sufficient account of overhead restrictions eg bridges and tunnels and other hazards, \nsuch as level crossings, which may present dangers fo\nr long vehicles?”. \n(Bold added)\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\nSeptember 2013\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n"